but this is not required or checked by $(D
kullbackLeiblerDivergence). If any element `bi` is zero and the
corresponding element `ai` nonzero, returns infinity. (Otherwise,
if $(D ai == 0 && bi == 0), the term $(D ai * log(ai / bi)) is
